<main>
    <div class="home-title">
        <h1>Secure Oil Price API Demo</h1>
    </div>

    <p>
        This INF 653 project is a secure API built with Node.js and Express.
        It protects oil price data using middleware.
    </p>

    <div class="about-container">
        <h2>What this project does</h2>
        <p>
            The API only returns data when security checks pass.
            Requests are validated by middleware before data is sent.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Middleware authentication</li>
            <li>IP filtering</li>
            <li>CORS control</li>
            <li>Bearer token verification</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="how-to-container">
        <h2>How to use this app</h2>
        <p>
            1) Send a request to the oil price endpoint. <br>
            2) Include a valid Bearer token in the Authorization header. <br>
            3) Send the request from an allowed IP. <br>
            4) Use an allowed origin so CORS check passes. <br>
        </p>
    </div>

    <p>
        This project is for learning API security with middleware.
    </p>
</main>